__HEADER__(`Octave Help')

<div class="section">
<p>The __MAILTO__(`help@octave.org', `help') mailing list exists for
the discussion of matters related to using and installing Octave.  If
would like to join the discussion, please visit the
<a href="http://www.cae.wisc.edu/mailman/listinfo/help-octave">list
subscription page</a> on the web.
</p>
<p>Messages sent to the list are also
__OCTAVE_HTTP__(`archive.html', `archived').</p>

<p>Please do <strong>not</strong> send requests to be added or removed
from the the mailing list, or other administrative trivia to the list
itself.</p>

<p>If you prefer to use a chat program instead of email, we also have
the __OCTAVE_HTTP__(`chat.html', `<tt>#octave</tt> IRC channel on Freenode'). You can either use <a
href="http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=octave&uio=MT1mYWxzZSYyPXRydWUmMTI9dHJ1ZQda">the
Freenode web client</a> to chat (just pick a screen name and answer
the CAPTCHA) or point your preferred <a
href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_Internet_Relay_Chat_clients">IRC
client</a> to <tt>irc.freenode.net</tt> and join the <tt>#octave</tt>
channel.</p>

<p>If you think you have found a bug in Octave or in the installation
procedure, however, you should submit a complete bug report to
__HTTP__(`bugs.octave.org', `the Octave bug tracker').  But before you
submit a bug report, please __OCTAVE_HTTP__(`bugs.html', `learn how to
submit a useful bug report').
</p>
</div>

